1
00:00:03,862 --> 00:00:06,531
Say you’re dealing with gold,

2
00:00:08,145 --> 00:00:12,704
you want to be a gold merchant or
be involved in the gold business,

3
00:00:12,977 --> 00:00:14,929
you could rephrase your question:

4
00:00:14,929 --> 00:00:21,947
“I don’t want to insult any of the people
who come presenting what they have.

5
00:00:21,947 --> 00:00:24,941
They think it’s gold. 
I don’t want to hurt anybody’s feelings.”

6
00:00:25,141 --> 00:00:28,368
[Reality Gems | Quantity and Quality]

7
00:00:28,907 --> 00:00:36,371
It will mean you will have to become acquainted 
with identifying what is gold

8
00:00:36,418 --> 00:00:40,204
and all of its levels, and if you can’t,

9
00:00:40,239 --> 00:00:43,408
then you can only work under the direction
of someone who does,

10
00:00:43,463 --> 00:00:46,524
who has that knowledge.

11
00:00:46,745 --> 00:00:51,255
So, there’s a way of determining
what is 24 carat gold,

12
00:00:51,425 --> 00:00:55,252
what is 22, 18, 14, 12 …

13
00:00:55,403 --> 00:01:01,023
What is gold plate, gold wash, gold leaf.
What’s imitation gold.

14
00:01:01,460 --> 00:01:05,417
So, just to say, “Well, I don’t want 
to insult any of the customers” …

15
00:01:05,417 --> 00:01:08,219
Yes, all right, there’s a tactful way
to explain to them,

16
00:01:08,219 --> 00:01:09,484
we have a process by which

17
00:01:09,484 --> 00:01:13,167
we can determine whether or not 
this is real gold or not.

18
00:01:15,411 --> 00:01:18,408
This is not a fantasy. 
I’ve done this in India before,

19
00:01:18,408 --> 00:01:20,865
you go to a goldsmith, 
and what do they do?

20
00:01:20,865 --> 00:01:23,434
They take the gold 
and they burn it under a lamp,

21
00:01:23,434 --> 00:01:26,378
and it’s covered in black soot, 
they wipe it off,

22
00:01:26,378 --> 00:01:28,536
and that’s what
a so-called touchstone is,

23
00:01:28,536 --> 00:01:30,159
and you scrape it against that,

24
00:01:30,159 --> 00:01:34,982
and there’s a way of determining 
what its actual value is.

25
00:01:34,982 --> 00:01:40,838
So, without becoming acquainted
with what it is,

26
00:01:40,838 --> 00:01:45,844
and the means of understanding and 
verifying what this substance is,

27
00:01:45,844 --> 00:01:51,261
then one is not in a position 
to represent it,

28
00:01:51,261 --> 00:01:54,726
or to make determinations with others.

29
00:01:54,726 --> 00:01:57,721
In either direction, good or bad.

30
00:01:58,344 --> 00:02:00,565
Therefore we’re told, 
you have to put yourself

31
00:02:00,565 --> 00:02:05,912
under the guidance of a vaiṣṇava, 
a substantial vaiṣṇava,

32
00:02:05,912 --> 00:02:08,863
who can determine, 
assess properly

33
00:02:08,863 --> 00:02:10,953
what is valuable,
what is not valuable;

34
00:02:10,953 --> 00:02:14,001
what is substantial, 
what is not substantial;

35
00:02:16,189 --> 00:02:20,125
what is imitation,
and what is real.

36
00:02:20,589 --> 00:02:26,424
But as once, after being asked 
so many questions,

37
00:02:26,424 --> 00:02:29,200
Śrīla Guru Mahārāj 
turned to the group of devotees,

38
00:02:29,200 --> 00:02:30,988
and said, 
“Can I ask you a question?”

39
00:02:30,988 --> 00:02:32,436
They’re like, “Why, sure!”

40
00:02:32,436 --> 00:02:35,809
and he said, 
“What is Kṛṣṇa consciousness?”

41
00:02:35,809 --> 00:02:41,548
and one person said, 
“It’s what Prabhupād taught us.”

42
00:02:41,561 --> 00:02:43,990
That was a good answer.

43
00:02:45,451 --> 00:02:50,441
And then someone else said,
“Bhakti”,

44
00:02:51,092 --> 00:02:56,673
and Guru Mahārāj at one point said,
“Did he say anything about Kṛṣṇa?”

45
00:02:56,673 --> 00:02:57,963
a little teasing.

46
00:02:57,963 --> 00:02:59,894
And then Guru Mahārāj 
just stopped the whole thing,

47
00:02:59,894 --> 00:03:02,920
he said, “It is reality!”

48
00:03:03,662 --> 00:03:05,307
It’s reality.

49
00:03:05,307 --> 00:03:08,006
And he said, 
“And it’s in your interest

50
00:03:08,006 --> 00:03:11,797
to become acquainted 
with that reality.”

51
00:03:11,797 --> 00:03:14,159
So, we’re back to this point:

52
00:03:14,159 --> 00:03:17,567
How do you determine
what is actual gold?

53
00:03:17,567 --> 00:03:24,223
Thailand’s famous for the nīlamaṇi,
the blue sapphire,

54
00:03:24,438 --> 00:03:28,968
but if you could go to a jeweller, 
they could show you

55
00:03:28,968 --> 00:03:34,045
a palmful of blue sapphires—
a hundred of them.

56
00:03:34,045 --> 00:03:36,594
Let’s just say they do, 
for example.

57
00:03:36,594 --> 00:03:39,729
One of them’s worth $35,000,

58
00:03:40,020 --> 00:03:42,867
one of them’s worth $3,500,

59
00:03:42,867 --> 00:03:45,258
one of them’s worth $350,

60
00:03:45,258 --> 00:03:48,025
and one of them’s worth $35.

61
00:03:49,087 --> 00:03:51,437
Which is which?

62
00:03:53,723 --> 00:03:58,124
So, some people will say,
and rightfully, from their perspective,

63
00:03:58,124 --> 00:04:00,879
“Well, they all look nice to me.”

64
00:04:01,144 --> 00:04:06,153
That’s not untrue. 
That’s true, they all look nice.

65
00:04:10,613 --> 00:04:14,726
Someone else may not care,
they’ll say, “What’s the difference?”

66
00:04:14,726 --> 00:04:18,355
There’s that type of level
of understanding also.

67
00:04:18,355 --> 00:04:23,830
But someone who’s in the market
for blue sapphires,

68
00:04:23,830 --> 00:04:25,470
it’s in their interest.

69
00:04:25,470 --> 00:04:28,772
Either they need to become acquainted
with how to identify,

70
00:04:28,772 --> 00:04:31,363
assess, the value of blue sapphires,

71
00:04:31,363 --> 00:04:34,692
or they’ve got to be in connection 
with somebody who does,

72
00:04:34,692 --> 00:04:36,206
or what’s going to happen?

73
00:04:36,206 --> 00:04:39,101
They’re going to be cheated.

74
00:04:39,594 --> 00:04:43,929
So, a $35 blue sapphire?

75
00:04:43,929 --> 00:04:46,808
They’re going to be told 
that it’s worth $35,000.

76
00:04:47,363 --> 00:04:50,729
So, it’s not that
we’re concocting these things,

77
00:04:50,744 --> 00:04:54,561
there are ways to determine that.

78
00:04:58,588 --> 00:05:02,607
So, in dealing with 
the plurality of currencies,

79
00:05:02,607 --> 00:05:04,395
someone shows up
with their money,

80
00:05:04,395 --> 00:05:11,153
if that’s your job, then of course
you don’t want to insult the clientelle,

81
00:05:11,153 --> 00:05:14,953
so you say, 
“Yes, we will happily accept your …”,

82
00:05:14,953 --> 00:05:17,684
and they’ll present something
and they may be surprised,

83
00:05:17,684 --> 00:05:20,977
“Oh! It only yields one of these.”

84
00:05:23,078 --> 00:05:26,431
That means quantity and quality.

